    <!-- History Section -->
    <section id="history">
        <h2>History</h2>
        <p><strong>Discovery:</strong> Hydrogen was first recognized as a distinct element in 1766 by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henry_Cavendish" target="_blank">Henry Cavendish</a>. His discovery revealed hydrogen as the lightest and most abundant element in the universe. It was later understood to be essential in the formation of stars.</p>
        <p>Hydrogenâ€™s role in the formation of stars is a crucial part of astrophysics, influencing the early universe's structure.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Uses Section -->
    <section id="uses">
        <h2>Uses</h2>
        <p>Hydrogen is a versatile element with a variety of uses in the real world, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Used in the production of ammonia for fertilizers in the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haber_process" target="_blank">Haber Process</a>.</li>
            <li>Hydrogen is a clean fuel used in hydrogen fuel cells, which produce electricity with water as the only byproduct.</li>
            <li>It is used in refining petroleum, producing methanol, and hydrogenating oils and fats.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Objects Section -->
    <section id="objects">
        <h2>Objects</h2>
        <p>In The Elemental Chronicles, Hydrogen is linked to the creation of the following notable artifacts:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="[[Hydrogen Orb - Object Page]]">Hydrogen Orb</a>: Created by <a href="[[Primus - Character Page]]">Primus</a> in the early days of the universe, this artifact harnesses the power of hydrogen to manipulate star formation.</li>
            <li><a href="[[Hydrogenic Sphere - Object Page]]">Hydrogenic Sphere</a>: A mystical object that controls the flow of hydrogen across various regions, used by the Aegis of the Noble in the early cosmic wars.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Locations Section -->
    <section id="locations">
        <h2>Locations</h2>
        <p>The element Hydrogen is tied to several significant locations in The Elemental Chronicles:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="[[Hydrogenic Temple - Location Page]]">Hydrogenic Temple</a>: An ancient structure where the first manipulation of hydrogen was recorded. It is located in the heart of the Elemental Nexus.</li>
            <li><a href="[[The Star Forge - Location Page]]">The Star Forge</a>: A sacred site where the hydrogen used in the creation of the first stars was harnessed by divine beings.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Characters Section -->
    <section id="characters">
        <h2>Characters</h2>
        <p>The following characters are closely linked to Hydrogen in The Elemental Chronicles:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="[[Primus - Character Page]]">Primus</a>: The First Star, who created the <a href="[[Hydrogen Orb - Object Page]]">Hydrogen Orb</a>, and played a vital role in the formation of the first celestial bodies.</li>
            <li><a href="[[Helion - Character Page]]">Helion</a>: The Star Lord of Helium, who often collaborated with Primus to stabilize early cosmic forces, including the use of Hydrogen in the creation of stars.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

